  "original_title": "QR Code  \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd  4 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "4 million people registered through QR Code",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesperson Minister Bandula Gunawardena said that the cabinet has given permission to appoint an advisory committee and a group of officials to ensure continuous supply of fuel, and said that people who are in crisis during the purchase of fuel will be able to purchase fuel easily from next month through the QR Code program.",
        "The minister said the above at the press conference announcing the Cabinet decisions held yesterday (26) at the Government Information Department.",
        "He said that the QR Code technology is currently being implemented very successfully and 40 lakh people have registered so far.",
        "He said that 70,123 vehicles received fuel at 245 fuel filling stations that implemented this system.",
        "He also said that in addition to the fuel filling stations that use this QR Code system, fuel is distributed to private buses, school services and ambulances through 107 depots.",
        "The Minister also said that the Petroleum Minister has asked the relevant authorities to register all the autos and agricultural machinery through the Police and Regional Secretaries of those provinces and arrange for the data to be made available to the Petroleum Ministry within the next two days.",
        "The Minister informed that fuel will be provided to the people despite the foreign exchange problems in the country and therefore requested to use fuel very sparingly."
      ],
